The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Poll raids net people amp; weapons

 April 11: Over 4,000 people have been arrested in Purulia, Bankura and West Midnapore as part of an exercise being carried out under the Election Commissions orders.

 Over 1,500 pieces of ammunition and 23 kg of explosives have also been found till April 9. In Bankura alone, over 2,000 people have been arrested since the central forces came in. 

 In West Midnapore, chief electoral officer Debashis Sen and deputy election commissioner Anand Kumar, who arrived from Bankura this afternoon, reviewed poll preparedness with district officials and constituency observers.

 On their way back, Kumar seized two cars being used by the Trinamul Congress candidate from Shalboni, Uttara Singh. She was unable to furnish the documents demanded .

 Curb on private cars

 Restrictions will be imposed on movement of even private cars on poll day, officials said. 

 Private vehicles will not be allowed to go within 200 met- res of a polling station. 

 However, taxis, autos, rickshaws and other commercial vehicles going to airports, stations, bus stands and hospitals will be allowed to ply.




